.TH MEOWPASS 1 "February 2025" "meowpass 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
meowpass \- generate secure, memorable passwords using cat names
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B meowpass
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B meowpass
generates secure, memorable passwords by combining random cat names with
various transformations including capitalization, digit insertion, and
symbol substitution. It includes analysis of password strength using
Shannon entropy, Kolmogorov complexity estimation, and pattern analysis.
.PP
The generator uses an embedded dictionary of 16,913 cat names to create
passwords that are both secure and easier to remember than purely random
strings.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-length " " \fINUM\fR
Set the target password length (default: 16, range: 8-128).
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-complexity " " \fINUM\fR
Set the complexity level from 1-10 (default: 5). Higher values result in
more character substitutions and transformations.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-count " " \fINUM\fR
Generate multiple passwords (default: 1).
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Show detailed complexity analysis for the generated password.
.TP
.BR \-\-copy
Copy the generated password to the system clipboard using xclip.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-psssst
Copy the generated password to the clipboard without displaying it.
This is more secure as the password won't be shown in clear text.
.TP
.BR \-\-test
Run the built-in test suite to verify correct operation.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.SH COMPLEXITY ANALYSIS
When run with the \fB\-v\fR option, meowpass displays:
.TP
.B Shannon Entropy
Information entropy in bits per character, measuring password randomness.
.TP
.B Compression Ratio
An approximation of Kolmogorov complexity based on run-length encoding,
indicating how compressible (and thus predictable) the password is.
.TP
.B Pattern Complexity
A score based on substring uniqueness within the password.
.TP
.B Character Diversity
Coverage across four character classes: lowercase letters, uppercase
letters, digits, and symbols.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Generate a default password:
.B meowpass
.TP
Generate a 24-character password with high complexity:
.B meowpass -l 24 -c 8
.TP
Generate 5 passwords with verbose analysis:
.B meowpass -n 5 -v
.TP
Generate and copy to clipboard:
.B meowpass --copy
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
Optional: xclip for clipboard support.
